-- Romanian Utility Apa Canal Seeks Bids for Water Upgrades
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2012-09-18T14:12:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-18/romanian-utility-apa-canal-seeks-bids-for-water-upgrades.html
Apa Canal SA, a Romanian water
utility, is seeking bids to upgrade sewage and water systems in
Brasov and Sibiu counties for about 92 million lei ($27
million).  Apa Canal plans to rehabilitate and expand a water supply
system in the town of Fagaras through a 64.4 million-lei
contract, European Union procurement  document s showed. Bids can
be submitted by Nov. 16.  The Sibiu utility is also seeking to expand and upgrade
water and wastewater systems in Cisnadie and the village of
Rasinari for 27.2 million lei. Bids must be made by Nov. 9.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
